Hello. The associative array .next and .prev methods propagate constants which causes g++ compilation errors.

## Working Example

```systemverilog
module t;

    typedef bit [7:0] data_t;
    data_t dict [data_t];

    initial begin
        data_t a;

        dict.first(a);
        dict.next(a);

        $finish;
    end

endmodule
```

## Argument with initial value causes g++ error

```systemverilog
module t;

    typedef bit [7:0] data_t;
    data_t dict [data_t];

    initial begin
        data_t a;

        a = 4; // set to number instead of .first
        dict.next(a);

        $finish;
    end

endmodule
```
